Simple Perl script to display ID3 tags from given files.

Usage:

    show-tags [dir]

Given a directory name, will show the ID3 tags for all files in that dir.

If no dir is given, all files in the current directory will be shown instead.

Example:

    [davidp@supernova:~]$ show-tags
    /shared/music/Complete\ Albums/Oasis\ -\ The\ Masterplan
    Track|Title                 |Artist|Album
    1    |Acquiesce             |Oasis |The Masterplan
    2    |Underneath The Sky    |Oasis |The Masterplan
    3    |Talk Tonight          |Oasis |The Masterplan
    4    |Going Nowhere         |Oasis |The Masterplan
    5    |Fade Away             |Oasis |The Masterplan
    6    |The Swamp Song        |Oasis |The Masterplan
    7    |I Am The Walrus (Live)|Oasis |The Masterplan
    8    |Listen Up             |Oasis |The Masterplan
    9    |Rockin' Chair         |Oasis |The Masterplan
    10   |Half The World Away   |Oasis |The Masterplan
    11   |(It's Good) To Be Free|Oasis |The Masterplan
    12   |Stay Young            |Oasis |The Masterplan
    13   |Headshrinker          |Oasis |The Masterplan
    14   |The Masterplan        |Oasis |The Masterplan


